  number    =  1589,
  pages     = "670--679",
  abstract  = "The social science literature contains numerous examples of human
               tribalism and parochialism-the tendency to categorize individuals
               on the basis of their group membership, and treat ingroup members
               benevolently and outgroup members malevolently. We hypothesize
               that this tribal inclination is an adaptive response to the
               threat of coalitional aggression and intergroup conflict
